{
  "_id": "fhSubStellarMist",
  "name": "Stellar Mist",
  "type": "consumable",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "folder": "fhSubSciFi000001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A pearlescent suspension that dissolves in air. The user experiences sensations from elsewhere — sometimes elsewhen — for the duration. Operators learn not to trust the visions, but everyone tries them once.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 1 hour you have advantage on Intelligence (Investigation) checks but disadvantage on Wisdom saving throws. If the Dynamic Active Effects module is active, you also gain a +1d4 bonus to all saving throws for the duration (the &ldquo;Insight&rdquo; layer).</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Stellar Mist (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Stellar Mist.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Wisdom (Insight) and Wisdom (Perception) checks.</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 3.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(3 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 2) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Neural Diffuser or Vapor Mask.</em></p>"
    },
